      <!-- Who Should Consider an F1 Loan -->
      <div class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Who Should Consider an F1 Loan?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          An F1 Loan may be suitable if you:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <li><strong>Desire High Flexibility:</strong> Want the ability to adjust your loan term and switch between interest-only and amortizing payments during annual adjustments.</li>
          <li><strong>Are Comfortable with Variable Rates:</strong> Prepared for payments that can change annually due to interest rate fluctuations.</li>
          <li><strong>Seek Potential Lower Payments:</strong> Looking for a loan that may offer lower initial payments compared to fixed-rate loans.</li>
          <li><strong>Can Manage Payment Increases:</strong> Confident in your ability to handle potential increases in monthly payments if interest rates rise.</li>
          <li><strong>Want to Utilize Interest-Only Periods Flexibly:</strong> Appreciate the option to decide when to use your interest-only periods throughout the loan term.</li>
        </ul>
